# Mitigating threats using Microsoft Defender XDR

## Objective
The objective of these notes is to understand how XDR threat protection works in Microsoft Sentinel and how it supports security monitoring and investigation.

## Summary
Analyze threat data across domains and rapidly remediate threats with built-in orchestration and automation in Microsoft Defender XDR. 

## Key Terms
| Microsoft Defender | Microsoft family of security products. Protects computers, users, email, identities, cloup apps and data. |
| XDR(Extended Detection and Response) | Security approach. Collects and correlates telemetry from multiple security areas, such as endpoints, identities, email, cloud apps, networks and SaaS services. Allows defenders to detect, investigate and respond to attacks from one place. |
| MDO | Microsoft's email and collaboration security product. Protects Exchange Online, Microsoft Teams, Sharepoint Online and OneDrive against phishing, malicious links, malware and business email compromise. Cloud-based email filtering service. |
| MDE | Enterprise endpoint security platform. Helps organizations prevent, detect, investigate and respond to advanced threats on endpoints. |
| Intune | Cloud-based endpoint management service. Manages and secures devices, apps and data. Manages user access to organizational resources across mobile devices, desktops and virtual endpoints. |
| Intune Compliance Policy | Set of rules and conditions used by Intune to decide whether a managed device is compliant or non-compliant. |
| Microsoft Entra ID | cloud-based identity and access management service. Handles user identity, authenticaiton, access control, policies and protection. |
| MEID Conditional Access Policy | Zero Trust policy engine, using signals to make and enforce access decisions. |
| CAE(Continuous Access Evaluation | Feature that lets access be re-evaluated in near real-time.  Responds to critical events and Conditional Access policy changes so access can be revoked or rechecked. | 
| Endpoint AV alerts | Anti-Virus alerts generated on endpoint devices. |
| TIP(Threat Intelligence Platform) | External threat intelligence product. Collects organizes threat intelligence. Helps teams manage IOCs. Capable of pushing data into tools like Sentinel for detection, hunting and enrichment. |
| REST API | API that follows the REST style for communication over the web. Client sends HTTP requests to server's resource URLs. Server returns responses in JSON. Stateless(each request must include the information needed for the server to process) |
| SDK(Software Development Kit) | bundle of tools and code that helps developers build applications for platforms or services. |
| Federated services | system/orgaization trusts another identity provider to authenticate users(instead of authenticating them locally). Collection of domains that have established trust. |
| KQL(Kusto Query Language) | Query language for searching/filtering/analyzing/summarizing large amounts of data. Used to explore data, discover patterns, identify anomalies, create statistical models. |

